# Wireframe Spec — Desktop and Mobile

## Scope
This spec defines a section-by-section wireframe for the homepage and maps each section to Desktop and Mobile structure, spacing, and behavior.

Accent color is locked:
- Accent: #A3E635

---

## Global Frame

Desktop (1024px+):
- max content width: 1200px
- container horizontal padding: 48px (1024-1439), 64px (1440+)
- section vertical rhythm: 112px baseline

Mobile (320-767px):
- container horizontal padding: 16px (320-374), 20px (375+)
- section vertical rhythm: 72px baseline
- all multi-column regions collapse to single column

Shared:
- sticky top nav
- skip link at top
- 8px spacing grid

---

## 0) Header / Sticky Nav

Desktop wireframe:
- Left: wordmark/name
- Center: anchors (Hero, Expertise, Projects, Philosophy, Contact)
- Right: GitHub, LinkedIn
- Height: 64-72px

Mobile wireframe:
- Left: wordmark/name
- Right: compact menu trigger + external icons
- Anchors in a slide-over panel or compact dropdown
- Height: 56-64px

Behavior:
- active section indicator uses lime accent under text or small dot
- nav surface adds mild blur on scroll

Acceptance:
- one-row nav on mobile
- all controls 44x44 minimum touch target

---

## 1) Hero

Desktop wireframe (12-col):
- Col 1-7: headline, supporting copy, CTA row
- Col 8-12: ambient visual module (grid/diagram/wave)
- Vertical align center in first viewport

Mobile wireframe:
- Stack order: headline -> support -> CTA row -> visual module
- visual module capped height to avoid pushing CTA too far below fold

Content bounds:
- headline <= 10 words
- supporting copy <= 24 words
- CTA count <= 3

Spacing:
- Desktop: 24-32px between headline and support, 24px to CTA
- Mobile: 16-20px between blocks

---

## 2) Expertise

Desktop wireframe:
- Section title row
- 3 equal cards in one row
- Each card: category title + 4-6 bullets

Mobile wireframe:
- Section title row
- 3 cards stacked
- card gap: 12-16px

Card frame:
- border + subtle surface lift
- optional tiny top indicator line in lime on active/hover

Acceptance:
- no bullet clipping/truncation at 320px
- focus ring clearly visible on interactive card elements

