## 5) Technical Philosophy

Desktop wireframe:
- center-weighted content block
- headline line
- supporting paragraph
- 2-column principles list (2-3 items each side)

Mobile wireframe:
- single-column stack
- principles as compact bullet list

Suggested principles:
- clarity over decoration
- performance as UX
- accessibility as baseline quality
- systemized components over ad hoc styling
- maintainability under growth

Acceptance:
- readable in one viewport desktop
- no jargon-heavy sentence blocks

---

## 6) Contact

Desktop wireframe:
- centered heading/prompt
- row of primary links (GitHub, LinkedIn, Email optional)
- minimal footer meta below

Mobile wireframe:
- same order, links stack or wrap
- footer remains single concise line

Acceptance:
- contact actions obvious within 2 seconds of arriving in section
- external links include visible focus and hover states

---

## Motion Wireframe Notes

Section reveals:
- slight fade + translateY (8-16px)
- stagger only within a section, not across whole page

Hover motion:
- card elevate max 4px
- timing 180-250ms

Reduced motion:
- keep opacity-only transitions or no movement

---

## QA Viewports

Validate layout and spacing at:
- 320x568
- 375x812
- 768x1024
- 1024x768
- 1440x900

Pass conditions:
- no horizontal scroll
- no overlap between text and visuals
- proof block hierarchy preserved
- CTA/buttons usable by keyboard and touch
